{"DOZE":[{"def":"To slumber; to sleep lightly; to be in a dull or stupefied condition, as if half asleep; to be drowsy.","pos":""}],"DOZEN":[{"def":"A collection of twelve objects; a tale or set of twelve; with or without of before the substantive which follows.","pos":""},{"def":"An indefinite small number.","pos":""}],"DOZER":[{"def":"One who dozes or drowses.","pos":""}],"DOZINESS":[{"def":"The state of being dozy; drowsiness; inclination to sleep.","pos":""}],"DOZY":[{"def":"Drowsy; inclined to doze; sleepy; sluggish; as, a dozy head.","pos":""}]}